snippet.textDisplay:
New World "frying" 3090s has nothing to do with New World and everything to do with EVGA screwing their PCB design. They simply used a crappy VRM controller that cant change power limits per rail via software and PCIe fuses that are too weak. Thus, if they want to lower PCIe PL they need to lower the total PL considerably so that PCIe transients dont trip the PCIe fuse.

They have finally recently released a new PCB revision that has a better VRM controller so they can actually change PLs per rail, but idk if they have lowered PCIe PL yet. They also havent increased the PCIe fuse yet either. PCIe fuse is 91w, PCIe PL is 75w, transients can easily get to 91w without issues. Note that a "375w" 3080 can hit 490w <1ms transients and a "275w" 2080Ti can hit 390w <1ms transients both quite easily. Transients going far above their software limit is nothing new and it very likely wont change.
